circumstances:
En route, aircraft went out of control and crashed in Rabenwald, some 36 km northeast of Graz. Four crew were rescued while seven others were killed. Exact circumstances unknown. 
Crew who were killed: 
Harry Moore, 
Bale Semack, 
James Richels, 
Gordon Thornton, 
Roy Reneau, 
James Milnes, 
George Stout. 
Taken prisoner: 
Walter Cates, 
Charles Freeman, 
Carl Shedlock, 
Francis Stack.
